documentation.text:
@dev Is there a contract with id _contractId.
 @param _contractId Id into contracts mapping.

newContract(address,string,address,uint2.details: Sender / Payer sets up a new hash time lock contract depositing the funds and providing the reciever and terms. NOTE: _receiver must first call approve() on the token contract.       See isApprovedOrOwner check in tokensTransferable modifier.

params._tokenId: Id of the token to lock up.

refund(uint256).details: Called by the sender if there was no withdraw AND the time lock has expired. This will restore ownership of the tokens to the sender.

params._contractId: Id of HTLC to refund from.

withdraw(uint256,string).details: Called by the receiver once they know the preimage of the hashlock. This will transfer ownership of the locked tokens to their address.

params._preimage: sha256(_preimage) should equal the contract hashlock.
